data.title: Danielle Newsholme, LCSW, Licensed Clinical Social Worker
data.meta_description: Danielle Newsholme, LCSW is a Jacksonville Licensed Clinical Social Worker for Baptist Health
data.text:
Danielle Newsholme, LCSW is a mental health therapist and qualified supervisor with Baptist Behavioral Health. Danielle specializes in maternal mental health, and she has worked with various populations throughout her professional tenure including geriatrics, children, adults and families. Danielleâ€™s passion is in family systems where she serves as an advocate to strengthen family connections while nurturing change and development. Her areas of expertise include:

Maternal Mental Health

Anxiety and Stress Management

Depression

Family Therapy

Parenting Issues

About Me

I have resided in Northeast Florida since 2009 when I moved here from upstate NY. My husband, our four children, and I enjoy being outside, especially when the weather is cooler. We enjoy fishing, camping, and walking nature trails. My mantra is to be grounded in the present and enjoy life in simple moments.

I grew up in an environment where family was the most important facet of life. I love working alongside clients who are adjusting to changing family dynamics and navigating how to be the best new version of themselves possible. I believe with enough support and encouragement anyone can thrive in their roles in life.
